## Evaluated and Rejected (this run)
- derivative (Rust): RUSTSEC-2024-0388. derive_more/derive-where/educe exist as alternatives.
- paste (Rust): RUSTSEC-2024-0436. pastey is maintained drop-in fork.
- backoff (Rust): RUSTSEC-2025-0012. backon is maintained replacement.
- async-std (Rust): RUSTSEC-2025-0052, discontinued. smol/tokio alternatives. Too massive.
- static_assertions (Rust): Rust const assert! replaces most use cases. Too small scope.
- hex (Rust): const-hex is faster drop-in replacement.
- fnv (Rust): fxhash/ahash are better alternatives. Too small.
- square/javapoet (Java): Palantir maintains active fork with latest Java features.
- tink-crypto/tink (Java): Split into maintained tink-crypto org repos.
- Apache Commons (Java): BeanUtils, Collections, DBCP, Net, Codec all actively maintained.
- asaskevich/govalidator (Go): Actively maintained (v11, recent commits).
- xml2js (npm): fast-xml-parser is maintained alternative (different API but covers use case).
- formidable (npm): v3 exists, maintained.
- node-cron, cron, bull, agenda (npm): All maintained.
- tough-cookie (npm): Maintained (v6.0.0).
- Python (tqdm, tabulate, prettytable, python-dotenv, Pillow): All maintained.

